    dc:creator "Balkenohl, Michael" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "On the female gonocoxites of Asian, Arabian, and African Clivinini with realignment of the Thliboclivina-, Physoclivina-, and Eoclivina-species groups, and notes on the higher systematics of the tribe Clivinini Rafinesque, 1815 (Coleoptera, Carabidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119957>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119963>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119959>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119975>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119977> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119957>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Clivina (subgenus Leucocara Bousquet, 2009) sacra Putzeys, 1875. External parts of the female reproductive tract in ventro-lateral delaminated view, highlighting some of the terms used in the descriptions." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119963>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7-25. Clivinini species, gonocoxites and epipleurites, ventro-lateral view. Shape A1. 7. Clivina (Clivina) fossor sachalinica Nakane, 1952, specimen from Sakhalin. 8. C. (C.) agona Putzeys, 1866, specimen from Banteay, Cambodia. 9. C. (C.) molucca Balkenohl, 2021, PT from Seram, Maluku. 10. C. (C.) helferi Putzeys, 1866, type spec. from Calcutta. 11. C. (C.) angularis Putzeys, 1867, type spec. from Calcutta. 12. C. (C.) mekongensis Lesne, 1896, specimen from Luang Prabang, Laos. 13. C. (L.) traquebarica Bonelli, 1813, type spec. from Indo China. 14. C. (L.) tutancamon Schatzmayr, 1936, specimen from Barrage, Egypt. 15. C. (Dacca) forcipata (Putzeys, 1861), specimen from Calcutta. 16. Ancus carniceps Andrewes, 1936, HT from Balor, Java. 17. Ancus excavaticeps Putzeys, 1867, specimen from Prek Toal, Cambodia. 18. Basilewskyana villiersi Basilewsky, 1948, specimen from Touba, Ivory Coast. 19. Clypeospinus validus (Andrewes, 1936), HT from Battaramulla, Sri Lanka. 20. Leleuporella mandibularis (Burgeon, 1935), specimen from Thuapa, Congo. 21. Rugiluclivina puncticollis Balkenohl, 1996, PT from Hanoi, Vietnam. 22. R. puncticollis, unmounted, ventral view. 23. Schizogenius freyi Baehr, 1983, HT from Vilu Levu, Fiji Islands. 24. S. sulcifrons Putzeys, 1846, specimen from Abercorn, USA. 25. S. neovalidus Whitehead, 1972, specimes from Aravaipa, Arizona." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119963/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119959>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Sulciclivina attenuata (Herbst, 1806). External parts of the female reproductive tract in ventro-lateral delaminated view, highlighting some of the terms used in the descriptions." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119959/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119975>
    dc:description "FIGURES 47-54. Clivinini species, gonocoxites and epipleurites, ventro-lateral view. Shape C. 47, 48. Coryza maculata Nietner, 1856, specimens from Nepal in mounted and unmounted view. 49. Halocoryza maindoniAlluaud, 1919, specimen from Aden, Yemen in unmounted view. 50. H. arenaria (Darlington, 1939), specimen from Barbados. 51. Lophocoryza sechellensis Basilewsky, 1973, PT from Ile Praslin, Seychelles, unmounted view. 52, 53. L. araticeps omanica Balkenohl, 2018, HT in enlarged detailed and delaminated view. 54. L. sciakyi Balkenohl, 2018, PT from Saint-Augustin, Madagascar." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119975/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119977>
    dc:description "FIGURE 55. Afrosyleter ituricus Basilewsky, 1959, specimen from Parc du Banco, Ivory Coast. Gonocoxites and epipleurite, ventro-lateral view. Shape D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119977/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

